  <h1 class="title topictitle1">$sort</h1>

  <div class="body">
    <div class="section"><h2 class="title sectiontitle">Description</h2>
      
      <p class="p">$sort Is used to specify the collation of the result set. Nested object using the dot operator(.) Reference field names.</p>

    </div>

    <div class="section"><h2 class="title sectiontitle">Example</h2>
      
    </div>

    <pre class="pre codeblock">db.collectionspace.collection.aggregate({$sort:{score:-1,name:1}});</pre>

    <p class="p">This operation represents tead records from the collection collection in the field and score values were sorted in descending order (1 indicates 
      ascendign, -1 means descending).</p>

    <p class="p">When the score between the record field values are the same, then the name field values in ascending order.</p>

  </div>

